# Showcase puzzle: per-player ACTION SCRIPT drives an active removal play.
#
# This puzzle exists to prove a capability that did NOT exist before
# task #16 / mtg-947: asserting an ACTIVE-card aspect (casting a targeted
# burn spell) in the bulk puzzle runner.
#
# Background: the bulk runner used to drive BOTH seats with the heuristic AI,
# which will not reliably cast a spell at a chosen target on cue. So puzzles
# could only test passive / combat-keyword cards. With an action script, P0 is
# driven by a RichInputController replaying semantic commands, so it casts
# Lightning Bolt at the opposing creature on turn 1 — deterministically.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Lightning Bolt in hand, 3 untapped Mountains on the battlefield.
#   - P1: a Grizzly Bears (2/2) on the battlefield.
#   - Script: P0 casts Lightning Bolt targeting the Grizzly Bears.
#   - Bolt deals 3 damage to a 2-toughness creature -> it dies (CR 120.6, 704.5g).
#
# The [p0_script] commands use the existing rich-input / fixed-input vocabulary
# (see docs/FIXED_INPUT_SYNTAX.md): `cast <card>` followed by `target <selector>`.
# Card-name matching is the same anti-overfitting semantic matcher used by
# `mtg tui --p1-fixed-inputs` (prefix / case-insensitive / space-insensitive),
# NOT brittle raw menu indices.
#
# Assertions (tracking issue: mtg-935 / mtg-947):
#   - Lightning Bolt was cast (spell cast Lightning Bolt)
#   - The Grizzly Bears died (creature died Grizzly Bears)
#   - It is now in P1's graveyard (opponent graveyard contains Grizzly Bears)

[metadata]
Name:Action Script - Lightning Bolt Kills a Creature
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 is driven by an action script that casts Lightning Bolt at P1's Grizzly Bears, killing it. Demonstrates that scripted active-card aspects (targeted burn) are now puzzle-testable in the bulk runner.

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Lightning Bolt
p0battlefield=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain
p0library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Cast Lightning Bolt targeting the Grizzly Bears. The inline `targeting`
# clause names the target semantically (anti-overfitting: by card name, not a
# raw menu index). When the Grizzly Bears is the only legal target the engine
# auto-selects it, and the clause is a harmless no-op; when there are several
# legal targets the controller uses the clause to pick the named one.
cast Lightning Bolt targeting Grizzly Bears

[assertions]
# The burn spell was actually cast by the script (active-card aspect).
spell cast Lightning Bolt
# 3 damage killed the 2/2 (CR 704.5g lethal damage state-based action).
creature died Grizzly Bears
# The dead creature is now in its owner's (P1's) graveyard.
opponent graveyard contains Grizzly Bears
